ould trigger a warning, especially when fetching unspecified user properties. Using \\\"testOnlyConfigProperty\\\" might be helpful, but I'm not sure if warnings about unknown properties would really be an issue. I see that `C3P0ConfigUtils.configFromFlatDefaults` can accept any value, yet `warnOnUnknownProperties` appears to only trigger during static initialization, not after refreshing. Default values like \\\"checkoutTimeout\\\" and \\\"maxPoolSize\\\" (which is 15) seem to be important points to keep in mind.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated coverage test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/src/test/java/com_mchange/c3p0/C3P0ConfigTest.java`\n\nCoverage added for:\n\n- `C3P0Config.findLibraryC3P0Config(...)`\n  - `Class.forName(...)`\n  - `Class#newInstance()`\n- `C3P0Config.bindUserOverridesAsString(...)`\n  - `Class#getMethod(...)`\n  - `Method#invoke(...)`\n\nThe new tests use public c3p0 APIs and avoid direct reflection in test code. I did not run compilation or tests, per workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07167361998f72a20169fc11a49aac8193ac892f971e55dc9d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 577, "output": 669, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27870, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778127255786, "responseId": "resp_07167361998f72a20169fc119837d48193b8f0d3bd76bb9b9a"}, "toolResults": []}
